Description: Used AXL Badwater Strat style electric guitar. In excellent condition, minimal fret-wear. All electronics cleaned up and in working order. Cleaned, restrung and completely set up and ready to play. Not sure of the year but appears to be from early 2010s from what I can tell. All cleaned up, re-strung and set up ready to go. This is the only example I found with the "Space Invaders" inlay on the fret board, so that makes it a bit unique. NOTE: Trem/whammy bar is NOT INCLUDED, missing. Badwater SRO AS 820 is the basic SRO AS model of the entire Badwater segment. This one features solid, double-cut body with flat top and bolt-on neck joint, 25-1/2" scale, 21-fret fingerboard, nickel hardware and satin finish on the body and neck. Body of this affordable Strat-like six-stringer is made of alder. Neck on this model is made of maple an it features the classic C contour in the back. 21-fret rosewood fingerboard is installed on it`s top. Three pickups on the body are installed in the H/S/S pattern. Non-locking tremolo bridge is in the back.
